Each election, the electoral body employs students, not just for help but also to teach them about the voting process. For full national and provincial results,Â click here. CAPE TOWN - It's not only IEC officials who make up the commission's workforce. Each election, the electoral body employs students -- not just for help, but also to teach them about the voting process.
The students are from various tertiary institutions and their backgrounds range from journalism to law. READ: IEC urgently investigating electoral irregularities But throughout these extremely busy few days, they all have a common goal: To help streamline the election process.
The students have become an integral part of the IEC's Results Centre for general elections for a number of years now.
So while the political winners are yet to be announced, for the students and the IEC it's a win-win situation.